tldr: The agent performed a thorough browser-based test of the application,
  covering the questionnaire flow, PDF report generation, and admin login error
  handling. It successfully validated PDF generation and login error messages,
  while also identifying and debugging a navigation issue within the
  questionnaire.
overview: The user tasked the agent with a comprehensive browser-based test of
  the application. The agent began by exploring the main questionnaire flow,
  initially encountering a perceived navigation issue with the "Next Section"
  button, which was later understood to be a rendering or scrolling artifact. To
  expedite testing, the agent utilized a "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)"
  button, successfully validating the report generation and PDF download
  functionality. Subsequently, the agent tested the admin dashboard, confirming
  that it was protected and that its login error handling worked as expected
  with an incorrect password. During manual questionnaire testing, the agent
  confirmed conditional fields were working but noted an unexpected behavior
  where the "Previous" button sometimes advanced to a later section, indicating
  a potential bug. The overall outcome was a thorough test of key application
  features, identifying both working functionalities and areas for further
  investigation.
